OL,3,CLabour vows to nationalise railways
OL,4,Cwithin five years if it wins election
OL,6,FThe government's own proposals for
OL,7,Frail reform, published in a draft Bill
OL,8,Fin February, include the creation of a
OL,9,Fnew public sector body named Great
OL,10,FBritish Railways (GBR) to hold
OL,11,Fresponsibility for rail infrastructure
OL,12,Fand awarding contracts to operate
OL,13,Ftrains.
OL,15,FBut Labour would create a "unified,
OL,16,Fpublicly owned, accountable and arm's
OL,17,Flength" version of GBR led by rail
OL,18,Fexperts rather than Whitehall, Ms
OL,19,FHaigh will say.
